  <h1 class="casename"><span class="RespondentName">THOMAS, ROBERT C.</span><br />
  <span class="supremeDocket">2004-1320</span> (La. <span class="Date">06/22/2004</span>) <span class="west">876 So.2d 53</span> <span class="Sanction">Permanent Resignation</span></h1>

  <p class="headingstyle">SUPREME COURT OF LOUISIANA</p>

  <p class="headingstyle">NO. 04-OB-1320</p>

  <p class="headingstyle">IN RE: ROBERT C. THOMAS</p>

  <p class="headingstyle">ORDER</p>

  <p class="bodycopy">The Office of Disciplinary Counsel ("ODC") is conducting an investigation into allegations that
  respondent mishandled the financial affairs of an elderly client.  Respondent now seeks to permanently resign from
  the practice of law in lieu of discipline.  The ODC has concurred in respondent's petition.</p>

  <p class="bodycopy">Having considered the Petition for Voluntary Permanent Resignation from the Practice of Law filed
  by Robert C. Thomas, Louisiana Bar Roll number 17827, and the concurrence thereto filed by the ODC,</p>

  <p class="bodycopy">IT IS ORDERED that the request of Robert C. Thomas for permanent resignation in lieu of
  discipline be and is hereby granted, pursuant to Supreme Court Rule XIX, § 20.1 and Rule 5.5(c) of the Rules of
  Professional Conduct, as amended March 24, 2004.</p>

  <p class="bodycopy">IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that Robert C. Thomas shall be permanently prohibited from practicing law
  in Louisiana or in any other jurisdiction in which he is admitted to the practice of law; shall be permanently
  prohibited from seeking readmission to the practice of law in this state or in any other jurisdiction in which he is
  admitted; and shall be permanently prohibited from seeking admission to the practice of law in any jurisdiction.</p>

  <p class="signature">NEW ORLEANS, LOUISIANA, this _____ day of June, 2004.</p>

  <p class="signature">FOR THE COURT:</p>

  <p class="signature">________________________________________</p>

  <p class="signature">JUSTICE, SUPREME COURT OF LOUISIANA</p>
